# MESSAGE: every cnv:Command must carry noun/verb/handler/doc/returnType/args and every cnv:Noun its rdfs:label + rdfs:comment + at least one cnv:hasCommand (translated from shapes.ttl sh:minCount; any row = a subject missing the bound ?missing property). Each UNION arm is scoped by FILTER(STRSTARTS(...)) to this pack's own cnv namespace: sync gates run against the UNION graph of every composed pack, and without the scope this gate would (and did) fire on other packs' subjects that merely share an rdf:type IRI shape.
PREFIX cnv:  <http://seanchatmangpt.github.io/packs/clap-noun-verb#>
PREFIX rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#>
SELECT ?s ?missing WHERE {
  {
    ?s a cnv:Command .
    FILTER(STRSTARTS(STR(?s), "http://seanchatmangpt.github.io/packs/clap-noun-verb#"))
    VALUES ?missing { cnv:noun cnv:verb cnv:handler cnv:doc cnv:returnType cnv:args }
  } UNION {
    ?s a cnv:Noun .
    FILTER(STRSTARTS(STR(?s), "http://seanchatmangpt.github.io/packs/clap-noun-verb#"))
    VALUES ?missing { rdfs:label rdfs:comment cnv:hasCommand }
  }
  FILTER NOT EXISTS { ?s ?missing ?any }
}
ORDER BY ?s ?missing
